# Cursor Rules for Next.js + Supabase + Drizzle + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
# Purpose: Enforce architecture, security, responsiveness, theming, and scalability.

You are an expert staff engineer building a production-grade healthcare web app.

========================================
HIGH-LEVEL PRINCIPLES
========================================
- Use Next.js App Router conventions.
- Supabase is the source of truth for Auth, Database, and Storage.
- Use Drizzle ORM for ALL database reads/writes from server code for type safety.
- Never expose Supabase service role keys to the client.
- Prefer server components and server actions for data mutations.
- Keep UI responsive across mobile/tablet/desktop, and support light + dark mode everywhere.
- Design RBAC to scale to new roles beyond doctor/nurse without refactoring.

========================================
TECH STACK CONSTRAINTS
========================================
- Next.js (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- shadcn/ui components as the primary UI kit
- Supabase Auth for session + user identity
- Supabase Storage for file storage
- Drizzle ORM for database access
- TypeScript strict mode

========================================
PROJECT STRUCTURE (SCALABLE)
========================================
Prefer this structure and keep boundaries clear:

/app
  /(public)
    page.tsx
  /(auth)
    sign-in/page.tsx
    sign-up/page.tsx
    reset-password/page.tsx
  /(app)
    layout.tsx
    dashboard/page.tsx
    settings/page.tsx
    admin/page.tsx            # optional
  /api
    /webhooks/supabase/route.ts
  /_actions
    auth.ts                   # server actions
    patients.ts
    uploads.ts   
  /_styles
    globals.css
  /_providers
    theme-provider.tsx
  /_lib
    auth/
      server.ts               # server auth helpers (get session, require role, etc.)
      client.ts               # client auth helpers (rare)
      rbac.ts                 # role/permission logic (scalable)
    db/
      drizzle/
        schema.ts
        index.ts              # db client instance
        queries/              # query modules
      supabase/
        server.ts             # createServerClient
        client.ts             # createBrowserClient
        middleware.ts         # SSR auth refresh helpers if used
    storage/
      index.ts                # storage helpers (upload/download)
    validation/
      zod.ts
    utils/
      cn.ts                   # tailwind merge
      dates.ts
/components
  ui/                         # shadcn if you prefer default path
  icons/
  layout/
  forms/
  tables/
/drizzle
  migrations/
/middleware.ts
/tailwind.config.ts
/next.config.js

Rules:
- Keep "db access" in /app/_lib/db/drizzle and never scatter SQL elsewhere.
- Keep RBAC logic centralized in /app/_lib/auth/rbac.ts.
- Put only route-level components in /app/*; reusable UI in /app/_components or /components.
- New roles must require NO new top-level route groups (no /(doctor) /(nurse) grouping).
  Use permissions and feature gating instead.

========================================
SUPABASE CLIENT RULES
========================================
- Client components may only use the public Supabase anon key, via createBrowserClient.
- Server components/actions must use createServerClient with cookies for auth.
- Only server-side code may use privileged access (service role key). Prefer RLS instead.

Do:
- Enforce Row Level Security (RLS) in Supabase for all tables.
- Use JWT claims / user metadata only as hints; permissions should be enforced via RLS + server checks.

Don’t:
- Don’t query Supabase directly from the client for protected data.
- Don’t embed service role keys in any code that can reach the browser.

========================================
DRIZZLE RULES
========================================
- Use Drizzle schema as canonical TypeScript types.
- Prefer typed query modules per domain:
  /app/_lib/db/drizzle/queries/<domain>.ts
- Keep migrations in /drizzle/migrations.
- Every new table must include:
  - id (uuid) primary key
  - created_at, updated_at timestamps where appropriate
  - organization_id if multi-tenant is planned (recommended)

========================================
AUTH + RBAC (SCALABLE)
========================================
Roles:
- Roles are data-driven, NOT hard-coded throughout the codebase.
- Only a single place defines roles/permissions mapping.

Implement:
- A "roles" table and/or a "user_roles" join table (supports multiple roles per user).
- A permissions model:
  - permission strings (e.g., "patients:read", "patients:write", "appointments:manage")
  - roles map to permissions
  - users receive roles (and thus permissions)

In code:
- Provide helpers:
  - requireUser()
  - requirePermission("patients:read")
  - can("permission") -> boolean
- UI gating uses can(), but server must enforce requirePermission() too.

Doctor/Nurse today:
- doctor, nurse roles exist as seeded data
- Adding new roles later must only require DB seed + mapping update in rbac config (not route rewrites)

========================================
ROUTING + PAGE ACCESS
========================================
- Use middleware.ts for coarse access control:
  - redirect unauthenticated users to /sign-in
  - optionally prevent access to /app routes without session
- Use server-side guards for fine-grained authorization:
  - server actions and server components must call requirePermission()

Do:
- Keep public pages in /(public), auth in /(auth), app behind auth in /(app).
- Use layouts to share navigation and theme providers.

========================================
UI / TAILWIND / SHADCN RULES
========================================
- All pages must be responsive by default.
  - Use mobile-first Tailwind: base styles for mobile, then sm/md/lg/xl.
  - Avoid fixed widths; use max-w-* + w-full.
  - Use responsive grids (grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 etc).

- Dark mode:
  - Use class-based dark mode ("dark") with ThemeProvider.
  - Every component must render correctly in both themes.
  - Prefer semantic tokens from shadcn (bg-background, text-foreground, border-border, etc).

- Accessibility:
  - All forms must have labels and validation messages.
  - Use aria attributes where needed.
  - Focus states must be visible.

========================================
SERVER ACTIONS / DATA MUTATION
========================================
- All mutations (create/update/delete) must be server actions or route handlers.
- Validate inputs with Zod in /app/_lib/validation.
- Return typed results and handle errors explicitly.

Pattern:
- server action -> validate -> requirePermission -> call Drizzle query -> return result

========================================
STORAGE (SUPABASE STORAGE)
========================================
- Use signed URLs for private files.
- Uploads happen server-side where possible (or via signed upload URLs).
- Store file metadata in DB (bucket, path, owner_id, created_at, etc).

========================================
ERROR HANDLING + LOGGING
========================================
- Use typed error objects; never swallow errors.
- Return user-friendly messages to UI; log internal details server-side.
- Avoid leaking sensitive data in errors.

========================================
TESTABILITY + MAINTAINABILITY
========================================
- Keep business logic outside React components.
- Prefer pure functions and query modules.
- Use consistent naming:
  - domain modules: patients, appointments, users, roles
  - components: PascalCase
  - server actions: verbNoun (createPatient)

========================================
DEFAULT CODE STYLE EXPECTATIONS
========================================
- TypeScript strict
- No any
- Prefer named exports in libs, default exports for Next pages/layouts
- Use eslint + prettier conventions if present
- Keep files small; split when >250-300 lines

========================================
OFFLINE SYNC + DRAFT PERSISTENCE (DEXIE) - REQUIRED FOR ALL FORMS
========================================

This app must be resilient to refreshes, navigation, and offline usage.

### Non-negotiable requirements
- **Never lose form input.** Any user-entered form data must persist automatically until a successful submit.
- **Offline-first submissions.** If a submit happens offline or fails due to network, the mutation must queue locally and sync later.
- Must work for **existing pages already built** and **all future forms**.

### Storage technology
- Use **Dexie (IndexedDB)** for drafts and outbox queues.
- Do NOT use localStorage for form data (except tiny UI prefs). Use IndexedDB for all drafts/outbox.

---

## 1) Drafts: auto-save + restore for every form

### Draft identity (scoping)
Every draft must be scoped by:
- `userId` (from Supabase session)
- `route` (pathname)
- `entityId` (optional, e.g. patientId/visitId)
- `formName` (stable string per form)

Draft primary key format:
- `${userId}:${formName}:${route}:${entityId ?? 'none'}`

### Draft behavior
- On mount: load draft and hydrate the form with `form.reset(draft.data)` (react-hook-form).
- On any field change: debounce (400–600ms) and persist to Dexie.
- Draft is cleared ONLY after confirmed successful submit.
- If user cancels editing, draft remains unless explicitly cleared.

### Required helper API
Implement and reuse these modules (do not reinvent per page):
- `app/_lib/offline/dexie.ts` (Dexie DB definition)
- `app/_lib/offline/drafts.ts` (save/load/clear)
- `app/_lib/offline/useFormDraft.ts` (react-hook-form integration)

### Rule for contributors
Any new form must include:
- `useFormDraft({ userId, route, entityId, formName, form })`

---

## 2) Outbox: offline queue + automatic sync

### When to queue
A mutation must be queued when:
- `navigator.onLine === false`, OR
- request throws a network error (fetch failed / timeout / DNS), OR
- server is unreachable (5xx is retryable)

Do NOT queue on:
- 4xx validation errors
- auth/permission errors

### Outbox operation schema
Each queued operation must have:
- `opId` (uuid; also used as idempotencyKey)
- `userId`
- `actionType` (string allow-listed on server)
- `payload` (JSON)
- `entityId` (optional)
- `route` (optional)
- `createdAt`
- `status`: queued | syncing | failed
- `retries`
- `lastError` (if failed)

### Idempotency rules
- Updates must be **idempotent** (repeat-safe).
- Creates must include a **client-generated UUID** as the row ID in payload so replays do not duplicate.
- Prefer server mutations that are safe when re-run with the same payload.

### Required helper API
Implement and reuse:
- `app/_lib/offline/outbox.ts` (enqueue/list/count/mark status)
- `app/_lib/offline/sync-engine.ts` (runner: FIFO, retry w/ exponential backoff, online event)
- `app/_lib/offline/submit-with-offline.ts` (single entrypoint for form submission)

### Sync trigger requirements
- Auto-sync on:
  - app mount (when authenticated)
  - `window.addEventListener('online', ...)`
  - interval while online (e.g. 20–30s)
- Process FIFO by `createdAt`.
- Retry with exponential backoff (cap at 60s), max ~8 retries.
- Mark permanent failures (4xx) as `failed` and do not retry.

---

## 3) Server dispatcher endpoint for queued ops

### Required endpoint
Create:
- `app/api/offline-sync/route.ts` (POST)

Request body:
- `{ opId, actionType, payload, idempotencyKey }`

Server responsibilities:
- Verify Supabase session server-side; if no session -> 401.
- Allow-list actionType values.
- Dispatch to the same Drizzle mutation functions used by the app.
- Never trust client role or userId; derive from session.
- Return `{ ok: true }` on success, `{ ok: false, error }` on failure.

---

## 4) Global sync status UI (minimal but required)

Create:
- `app/_components/offline-sync-indicator.tsx`
- `app/_lib/offline/useSyncStatus.ts`

UI must show:
- Online/Offline status
- Pending outbox count
- Syncing state
- Failed count (optionally opens a small Dialog listing failed ops and “Retry now”)

Mount it in the main authenticated app layout.

Use shadcn/ui components:
- Badge, Button, Dialog, ScrollArea, Separator, Toast

---

## 5) Mandatory: apply to existing pages too
When modifying or creating any form page:
- Add draft persistence via `useFormDraft`.
- Replace direct mutation calls with `submitWithOffline(...)`.
- Ensure drafts clear only on confirmed success.

No exceptions.


========================================
WHEN GENERATING NEW CODE
========================================
Always:
1) Place code in correct folder based on boundaries.
2) Add RBAC enforcement in server actions/routes.
3) Ensure responsive design (mobile-first Tailwind).
4) Ensure dark mode styles work.
5) Use Drizzle types and Zod validation.
6) Prefer shadcn/ui components when possible.

If unclear, make reasonable assumptions aligned with this architecture and proceed.
